      "slug": "nab",
      "title": "NAB",
      "tagline": "Create Efficient Merchant Experiences for Small Businesses",
      "thumb": "https://www.quynhdo.ca/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/IMG_7675-scaled.jpg",
      "cardImage": "https://www.quynhdo.ca/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/home.jpg",
      "summary": [
        "At NAB, I worked on designing merchant solutions for small businesses across Australia and New Zealand, focusing on improving both customer-facing payment experiences and internal banking systems.\n  \n\n  \n\nMy role involved enhancing the digital merchant experience across NAB’s payment and commerce ecosystem, including EFTPOS, online payments, and merchant onboarding journeys. I collaborated closely with product managers, engineers, and business stakeholders to simplify complex workflows, improve usability, and create more seamless experiences for business customers.\n\n  \n\nAlongside customer-facing improvements, I also contributed to optimizing internal banker tools and operational systems to help support teams manage merchant services more efficiently. This included identifying friction points in existing workflows, streamlining service processes, and designing scalable experiences that balanced business goals with customer needs.\n\n  \n\nDue to the nature of the work and company confidentiality, I’m limited in what I can publicly share. However, beyond product delivery, I contributed to several initiatives focused on accessibility, AI enablement, and design education within the organization. If you'd like to learn more, please feel free to contact me on Linkedin or Email."
